The 65th annual Grammy awards took place in LA on Sunday and the likes of Harry Styles and Adele were among the winners. Beyoncé was just one artist to make history at the bash when she became the most decorated artist in Grammys’ history, while Kim Petras became the first trans woman to scoop a coveted gong and Sam Smith the first non-binary artist to do so. The hitmakers wona Grammy for best pop duo during the ceremony. Queen Bey took her total Grammy wins up to 32 – leapfrogging the previous holder of the record, conductor Georg Solti. Adele took home the award for best pop solo performance, thanks to her iconic track Easy On Me while Harry won the coveted album of the year award. Elsewhere, Lizzo’s About Damn Time was crowned record of the year and song of the year went to Bonnie Raitt for hit Just Like That. Check out the full winners’ list below. Got a story? If you’ve got a celebrity story, video or pictures get in touch with the Metro.co.uk entertainment team by emailing us celebtips@metro.co.uk, calling 020 3615 2145 or by visiting our Submit Stuff page – we’d love to hear from you. MORE : Trevor Noah can’t resist mocking Prince Harry and his ‘frostbitten penis’ in savage roast at Grammys MORE : Who is Kathleen in The Last of Us, was she in the video game and who plays her?   You can follow our new Snapchat show Pop Cultur’d, the go-to place for all things pop culture. Keep up with the latest Showbiz exclusives by following Metro Showbiz on Snapchat. And football fans can indulge in all the transfer gossip and more on Metro Football on Snapchat.